...Out of 17 total wharfs in Western Area Urban, 16 have been identified under a social mobilization team security review as having a high to medium threat rating....
...Community ownership has proved to be a critical success factor in the Ebola response and IOM is placing an increased focus on deepening community engagement....IOM staffers are responsible for mentoring local health care workers on advanced health screening and IPC protocols to ensure patients who may be symptomatic are picked up immediately, while maintaining staff safety....
According to Dr. Teresa Zakaria, who is leading the IOM HQ team, "It is essential to properly articulate population flows on the border and ensure interventions are multi-sectoral, so that mobility becomes an integrated component of the Ebola emergency response. It is only natural that when you tell someone no, they will seek an alternative place to dock a boat or to enter a community. So it is equally important to be sensitive to local realities and tap into local knowledge....more]"

